attackStart(uint256,uint256).details: This function assumes the ReentrancyAttack contract is the owner of the Vaultis instance.It attempts to recursively withdraw funds up to a specified maximum recursion depth.The `ownerWithdraw` function in Vaultis uses a gas limit (200,000) for external calls,which will naturally limit the depth of reentrancy.

params.amount: The amount of ETH to withdraw in each reentrant call.
params.maxRecursions: The maximum number of recursive calls to attempt.

constructor.details: Initializes the target Vaultis contract address.

params._vaultisAddress: The address of the Vaultis contract to attack.

withdrawEther().details: This is a safety function to recover funds from the attack contract.

attackStart(uint256,uint256).notice: Initiates a controlled reentrancy attack on the Vaultis contract's `ownerWithdraw` function.

owner().notice: The owner of this ReentrancyAttack contract.

vaultis().notice: The instance of the Vaultis contract that this contract will attempt to attack.

withdrawEther().notice: Allows the owner to withdraw any ETH held by this contract.
